This paper is primarily focused on social choice theory, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). The paper also involves statistical learning and hypothesis testing, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of sampling and the analysis of sample complexity are relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper also involves simulations and empirical analysis, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
